 B2(N2), with an abundance at least 1.7 times lower\nthan that of $n$-C$_3$H$_7$CN. This value is within the range predicted by the\nchemical models. The models indicate that the degree of branching rises with\nincreasing molecular size. The efficiency of CN addition to unsaturated\nhydrocarbons boosts the abundances of nitriles in the model, and enhances the\nratio of straight-to-branched molecule production. The predicted abundance of\n$s$-C$_4$H$_9$CN makes it a good candidate for future detection toward Sgr\nB2(N2).\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 25 Jan 2017 04:57:38 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-05-03"}
